169inline int64_t CpRandomSeed() {
170 return absl::GetFlag(FLAGS_cp_random_seed) == -1
171 ? absl::Uniform<int64_t>(absl::BitGen(), 0, kint64max)
172 : absl::GetFlag(FLAGS_cp_random_seed);
173}

1077 // All factories (MakeXXX methods) encapsulate creation of objects
1078 // through RevAlloc(). Hence, the Solver used for allocating the
1079 // returned object will retain ownership of the allocated memory.
1080 // Destructors are called upon backtrack, or when the Solver is
1081 // itself destructed.

1220 template <typename F>
1221 Constraint* MakeLightElement(F values, IntVar* const var, IntVar* const index,
1222 std::function<bool()> deep_serialize = nullptr) {
1223 return RevAlloc(new LightIntFunctionElementCt<F>(
1224 this, var, index, std::move(values), std::move(deep_serialize)));
1225 }

1233 template <typename F>
1234 Constraint* MakeLightElement(F values, IntVar* const var,
1235 IntVar* const index1, IntVar* const index2,
1236 std::function<bool()> deep_serialize = nullptr) {
1237 return RevAlloc(new LightIntIntFunctionElementCt<F>(
1238 this, var, index1, index2, std::move(values),
1239 std::move(deep_serialize)));
1240 }

2347 : absl::Milliseconds(time_in_ms));
2348 }

2949 template <class T>
2950 void SaveAndSetValue(T* adr, T val) {
2951 if (*adr != val) {
2952 InternalSaveValue(adr);
2953 *adr = val;
2954 }
2955 }
2956
2958 template <class T>
2959 void SaveAndAdd(T* adr, T val) {
2960 if (val != 0) {
2961 InternalSaveValue(adr);
2962 (*adr) += val;
2963 }
2964 }

3934template <class T>
3935class Rev {
3936 public:
3937 explicit Rev(const T& val) : stamp_(0), value_(val) {}
3938
3939 const T& Value() const { return value_; }
3940
3941 void SetValue(Solver* const s, const T& val) {
3942 if (val != value_) {
3943 if (stamp_ < s->stamp()) {
3944 s->SaveValue(&value_);
3945 stamp_ = s->stamp();
3946 }
3947 value_ = val;
3948 }
3949 }
3950
3951 private:
3952 uint64_t stamp_;
3953 T value_;
3954};
3955
3957template <class T>
3958class NumericalRev : public Rev<T> {
3959 public:
3960 explicit NumericalRev(const T& val) : Rev<T>(val) {}
3961
3962 void Add(Solver* const s, const T& to_add) {
3963 this->SetValue(s, this->Value() + to_add);
3964 }
3965
3966 void Incr(Solver* const s) { Add(s, 1); }
3967
3968 void Decr(Solver* const s) { Add(s, -1); }
3969};
3970
3976template <class T>
3977class RevArray {
3978 public:
3979 RevArray(int size, const T& val)
3980 : stamps_(new uint64_t[size]), values_(new T[size]), size_(size) {
3981 for (int i = 0; i < size; ++i) {
3982 stamps_[i] = 0;
3983 values_[i] = val;
3984 }
3985 }
3986
3987 ~RevArray() {}
3988
3989 int64_t size() const { return size_; }
3990
3991 const T& Value(int index) const { return values_[index]; }
3992
3993#if !defined(SWIG)
3994 const T& operator[](int index) const { return values_[index]; }
3995#endif
3996
3997 void SetValue(Solver* const s, int index, const T& val) {
3998 DCHECK_LT(index, size_);
3999 if (val != values_[index]) {
4000 if (stamps_[index] < s->stamp()) {
4001 s->SaveValue(&values_[index]);
4002 stamps_[index] = s->stamp();
4003 }
4004 values_[index] = val;
4005 }
4006 }
4007
4008 private:
4009 std::unique_ptr<uint64_t[]> stamps_;
4010 std::unique_ptr<T[]> values_;
4011 const int size_;
4012};
4013
4015template <class T>
4016class NumericalRevArray : public RevArray<T> {
4017 public:
4018 NumericalRevArray(int size, const T& val) : RevArray<T>(size, val) {}
4019
4020 void Add(Solver* const s, int index, const T& to_add) {
4021 this->SetValue(s, index, this->Value(index) + to_add);
4022 }
4023
4024 void Incr(Solver* const s, int index) { Add(s, index, 1); }
4025
4026 void Decr(Solver* const s, int index) { Add(s, index, -1); }
4027};

4137#ifndef SWIG
4144class InitAndGetValues {
4145 public:
4146 explicit InitAndGetValues(IntVarIterator* it)
4147 : it_(it), begin_was_called_(false) {
4148 it_->Init();
4149 }
4150 struct Iterator;
4151
4152 Iterator begin() {
4153 if (DEBUG_MODE) {
4154 DCHECK(!begin_was_called_);
4155 begin_was_called_ = true;
4156 }
4157 return Iterator::Begin(it_);
4158 }
4159 Iterator end() { return Iterator::End(it_); }
4160
4161 struct Iterator {
4163 static Iterator Begin(IntVarIterator* it) {
4164 return Iterator(it, /*is_end=*/false);
4165 }
4166 static Iterator End(IntVarIterator* it) {
4167 return Iterator(it, /*is_end=*/true);
4168 }
4169
4170 int64_t operator*() const {
4171 DCHECK(it->Ok());
4172 return it->Value();
4173 }
4174 Iterator& operator++() {
4175 DCHECK(it->Ok());
4176 it->Next();
4177 return *this;
4178 }
4179 bool operator!=(const Iterator& other) const {
4180 DCHECK(other.it == it);
4181 DCHECK(other.is_end);
4182 return it->Ok();
4183 }
4184
4185 private:
4186 Iterator(IntVarIterator* it, bool is_end) : it(it), is_end(is_end) {}
4187
4188 IntVarIterator* const it;
4189 const bool is_end;
4190 };
4191
4192 private:
4193 IntVarIterator* const it_;
4194 bool begin_was_called_;
4195};
4196#endif // SWIG

4422// Base objective monitor class. All metaheuristics derive from this.
4423class ObjectiveMonitor : public SearchMonitor {
4424 public:
4425 ObjectiveMonitor(Solver* solver, const std::vector<bool>& maximize,
4426 std::vector<IntVar*> vars, std::vector<int64_t> steps);
4427 ~ObjectiveMonitor() override {}
4428#ifndef SWIG
4429 ObjectiveMonitor(const ObjectiveMonitor&) = delete;
4430 ObjectiveMonitor& operator=(const ObjectiveMonitor&) = delete;
4431#endif // SWIG
4432 IntVar* ObjectiveVar(int index) const { return objective_vars_[index]; }
4433 IntVar* MinimizationVar(int index) const { return minimization_vars_[index]; }
4434 int64_t Step(int index) const { return steps_[index]; }
4435 bool Maximize(int index) const {
4436 return ObjectiveVar(index) != MinimizationVar(index);
4437 }
4438 int64_t BestValue(int index) const {
4439 return Maximize(index) ? CapOpp(BestInternalValue(index))
4440 : BestInternalValue(index);
4441 }
4442 int Size() const { return objective_vars_.size(); }
4443 void EnterSearch() override;
4444 bool AtSolution() override;
4445 bool AcceptDelta(Assignment* delta, Assignment* deltadelta) override;
4446 void Accept(ModelVisitor* visitor) const override;
4447
4448 protected:
4449 const std::vector<IntVar*>& objective_vars() const { return objective_vars_; }
4450 const std::vector<IntVar*>& minimization_vars() const {
4451 return minimization_vars_;
4452 }
4453 int64_t BestInternalValue(int index) const { return best_values_[index]; }
4454 int64_t CurrentInternalValue(int index) const {
4455 return current_values_[index];
4456 }
4457 void SetCurrentInternalValue(int index, int64_t value) {
4458 current_values_[index] = value;
4459 }
4460 template <typename T>
4461 void MakeMinimizationVarsLessOrEqualWithSteps(const T& upper_bounds) {
4462 if (Size() == 1) {
4463 MinimizationVar(0)->SetMax(CapSub(upper_bounds(0), Step(0)));
4464 } else {
4465 Solver* const solver = this->solver();
4466 for (int i = 0; i < Size(); ++i) {
4467 upper_bounds_[i] = solver->MakeIntConst(upper_bounds(i));
4468 }
4469 solver->AddConstraint(solver->MakeLexicalLessOrEqualWithOffsets(
4470 minimization_vars_, upper_bounds_, steps_));
4471 }
4472 }
4473 template <typename T>
4474 IntVar* MakeMinimizationVarsLessOrEqualWithStepsStatus(
4475 const T& upper_bounds) {
4476 Solver* const solver = this->solver();
4477 IntVar* status = solver->MakeBoolVar();
4478 if (Size() == 1) {
4479 solver->AddConstraint(solver->MakeIsLessOrEqualCstCt(
4480 MinimizationVar(0), CapSub(upper_bounds(0), Step(0)), status));
4481 } else {
4482 for (int i = 0; i < Size(); ++i) {
4483 upper_bounds_[i] = solver->MakeIntConst(upper_bounds(i));
4484 }
4485 solver->AddConstraint(solver->MakeIsLexicalLessOrEqualWithOffsetsCt(
4486 minimization_vars_, upper_bounds_, steps_, status));
4487 }
4488 return status;
4489 }
4490 bool CurrentInternalValuesAreConstraining() const;
4491
4492 bool found_initial_solution_;
4493
4494 private:
4495 friend class Solver;
4496 const std::vector<IntVar*> objective_vars_;
4497 std::vector<IntVar*> minimization_vars_;
4498 std::vector<IntVar*> upper_bounds_;
4499 std::vector<int64_t> steps_;
4500 std::vector<int64_t> best_values_;
4501 std::vector<int64_t> current_values_;
4502};

4650
4651// Limit based on the improvement rate of 'objective_var' or a lexicographic
4652// objective composed of 'objective_vars'.
4653// This limit proceeds in two stages:
4654// 1) During the phase of the search in which the objective is strictly
4655// improving, a threshold value is computed as the minimum improvement rate of
4656// the objective, based on the 'improvement_rate_coefficient' and
4657// 'improvement_rate_solutions_distance' parameters.
4658// 2) Then, if the search continues beyond this phase of strict improvement, the
4659// limit stops the search when the improvement rate of the objective gets below
4660// this threshold value.
4661class ImprovementSearchLimit : public SearchLimit {
4662 public:
4663 ImprovementSearchLimit(Solver* solver, IntVar* objective_var, bool maximize,
4664 double objective_scaling_factor,
4665 double objective_offset,
4666 double improvement_rate_coefficient,
4667 int improvement_rate_solutions_distance);
4668 ImprovementSearchLimit(Solver* solver, std::vector<IntVar*> objective_vars,
4669 std::vector<bool> maximize,
4670 std::vector<double> objective_scaling_factors,
4671 std::vector<double> objective_offsets,
4672 double improvement_rate_coefficient,
4673 int improvement_rate_solutions_distance);
4674 ~ImprovementSearchLimit() override;
4675 void Copy(const SearchLimit* limit) override;
4676 SearchLimit* MakeClone() const override;
4677 bool CheckWithOffset(absl::Duration offset) override;
4678 bool AtSolution() override;
4679 void Init() override;
4680 void Install() override;
4681
4682 private:
4683 std::vector<IntVar*> objective_vars_;
4684 std::vector<bool> maximize_;
4685 std::vector<double> objective_scaling_factors_;
4686 std::vector<double> objective_offsets_;
4687 double improvement_rate_coefficient_;
4688 int improvement_rate_solutions_distance_;
4689
4690 std::vector<double> best_objectives_;
4691 // clang-format off
4692 std::vector<std::deque<std::pair<double, int64_t> > > improvements_;
4693 // clang-format on
4694 std::vector<double> thresholds_;
4695 bool objective_updated_;
4696 bool gradient_stage_;
4697};

4967class IntVarElement : public AssignmentElement {
4968 public:
4969 IntVarElement();
4970 explicit IntVarElement(IntVar* var);
4971 void Reset(IntVar* var);
4972 IntVarElement* Clone();
4973 void Copy(const IntVarElement& element);
4974 IntVar* Var() const { return var_; }
4975 void Store() {
4976 min_ = var_->Min();
4977 max_ = var_->Max();
4978 }
4979 void Restore() {
4980 if (var_ != nullptr) {
4981 var_->SetRange(min_, max_);
4982 }
4983 }
4984 void LoadFromProto(const IntVarAssignment& int_var_assignment_proto);
4985 void WriteToProto(IntVarAssignment* int_var_assignment_proto) const;
4986
4987 int64_t Min() const { return min_; }
4988 void SetMin(int64_t m) { min_ = m; }
4989 int64_t Max() const { return max_; }
4990 void SetMax(int64_t m) { max_ = m; }
4991 int64_t Value() const {
4992 DCHECK_EQ(min_, max_);
4993 // Get the value from an unbound int var assignment element.
4994 return min_;
4995 }
4996 bool Bound() const { return (max_ == min_); }
4997 void SetRange(int64_t l, int64_t u) {
4998 min_ = l;
4999 max_ = u;
5000 }
5001 void SetValue(int64_t v) {
5002 min_ = v;
5003 max_ = v;
5004 }
5005 std::string DebugString() const;
5006
5007 bool operator==(const IntVarElement& element) const;
5008 bool operator!=(const IntVarElement& element) const {
5009 return !(*this == element);
5010 }
5011
5012 private:
5013 IntVar* var_;
5014 int64_t min_;
5015 int64_t max_;
5016};

5173
5174template <class V, class E>
5175class AssignmentContainer {
5176 public:
5177 AssignmentContainer() {}
5178 E* Add(V* var) {
5179 CHECK(var != nullptr);
5180 int index = -1;
5181 if (!Find(var, &index)) {
5182 return FastAdd(var);
5183 } else {
5184 return &elements_[index];
5185 }
5186 }
5188 E* FastAdd(V* var) {
5189 DCHECK(var != nullptr);
5190 elements_.emplace_back(var);
5191 return &elements_.back();
5192 }
5195 E* AddAtPosition(V* var, int position) {
5196 elements_[position].Reset(var);
5197 return &elements_[position];
5198 }
5199 void Clear() {
5200 elements_.clear();
5201 if (!elements_map_.empty()) {
5202 elements_map_.clear();
5203 }
5204 }
5207 void Resize(size_t size) { elements_.resize(size); }
5208 bool Empty() const { return elements_.empty(); }
5211 void CopyIntersection(const AssignmentContainer<V, E>& container) {
5212 for (int i = 0; i < container.elements_.size(); ++i) {
5213 const E& element = container.elements_[i];
5214 const V* const var = element.Var();
5215 int index = -1;
5216 if (i < elements_.size() && elements_[i].Var() == var) {
5217 index = i;
5218 } else if (!Find(var, &index)) {
5219 continue;
5220 }
5221 DCHECK_GE(index, 0);
5222 E* const local_element = &elements_[index];
5223 local_element->Copy(element);
5224 if (element.Activated()) {
5225 local_element->Activate();
5226 } else {
5227 local_element->Deactivate();
5228 }
5229 }
5230 }
5233 void Copy(const AssignmentContainer<V, E>& container) {
5234 Clear();
5235 for (int i = 0; i < container.elements_.size(); ++i) {
5236 const E& element = container.elements_[i];
5237 FastAdd(element.Var())->Copy(element);
5238 }
5239 }
5240 bool Contains(const V* const var) const {
5241 int index;
5242 return Find(var, &index);
5243 }
5244 E* MutableElement(const V* const var) {
5245 E* const element = MutableElementOrNull(var);
5246 DCHECK(element != nullptr)
5247 << "Unknown variable " << var->DebugString() << " in solution";
5248 return element;
5249 }
5250 E* MutableElementOrNull(const V* const var) {
5251 int index = -1;
5252 if (Find(var, &index)) {
5253 return MutableElement(index);
5254 }
5255 return nullptr;
5256 }
5257 const E& Element(const V* const var) const {
5258 const E* const element = ElementPtrOrNull(var);
5259 DCHECK(element != nullptr)
5260 << "Unknown variable " << var->DebugString() << " in solution";
5261 return *element;
5262 }
5263 const E* ElementPtrOrNull(const V* const var) const {
5264 int index = -1;
5265 if (Find(var, &index)) {
5266 return &Element(index);
5267 }
5268 return nullptr;
5269 }
5270 const std::vector<E>& elements() const { return elements_; }
5271 E* MutableElement(int index) { return &elements_[index]; }
5272 const E& Element(int index) const { return elements_[index]; }
5273 int Size() const { return elements_.size(); }
5274 void Store() {
5275 for (E& element : elements_) {
5276 element.Store();
5277 }
5278 }
5279 void Restore() {
5280 for (E& element : elements_) {
5281 if (element.Activated()) {
5282 element.Restore();
5283 }
5284 }
5285 }
5286 bool AreAllElementsBound() const {
5287 for (const E& element : elements_) {
5288 if (!element.Bound()) return false;
5289 }
5290 return true;
5291 }
5292
5296 bool operator==(const AssignmentContainer<V, E>& container) const {
5298 if (Size() != container.Size()) {
5299 return false;
5300 }
5302 EnsureMapIsUpToDate();
5306 for (const E& element : container.elements_) {
5307 const int position =
5308 gtl::FindWithDefault(elements_map_, element.Var(), -1);
5309 if (position < 0 || elements_[position] != element) {
5310 return false;
5311 }
5312 }
5313 return true;
5314 }
5315 bool operator!=(const AssignmentContainer<V, E>& container) const {
5316 return !(*this == container);
5317 }
5318
5319 private:
5320 void EnsureMapIsUpToDate() const {
5321 absl::flat_hash_map<const V*, int>* map =
5322 const_cast<absl::flat_hash_map<const V*, int>*>(&elements_map_);
5323 for (int i = map->size(); i < elements_.size(); ++i) {
5324 (*map)[elements_[i].Var()] = i;
5325 }
5326 }
5327 bool Find(const V* const var, int* index) const {
5329 const size_t kMaxSizeForLinearAccess = 11;
5330 if (Size() <= kMaxSizeForLinearAccess) {
5334 for (int i = 0; i < elements_.size(); ++i) {
5335 if (var == elements_[i].Var()) {
5336 *index = i;
5337 return true;
5338 }
5339 }
5340 return false;
5341 } else {
5342 EnsureMapIsUpToDate();
5343 DCHECK_EQ(elements_map_.size(), elements_.size());
5344 return gtl::FindCopy(elements_map_, var, index);
5345 }
5346 }
5347
5348 std::vector<E> elements_;
5349 absl::flat_hash_map<const V*, int> elements_map_;
5350};

5405 objective_elements_.reserve(vars.size());

5430 SetObjectiveValueFromIndex(0, value);
5431 }

5434 }

5436 return HasObjectiveFromIndex(index) ? objective_elements_[index].Min() : 0;
